crew must leave the ship, and hence as the boat steerer or harpooneer is of the 
number, that subordinate is the steersman upon the occasion, and the captain, 
having no place to sit in, is pulled off to his visit all standing like a pine 
tree. And often you will notice that being conscious of the eyes of the whole 
